items.title: Ep. 421 - On to #GW2 - Square Peg in an Ass-Hole

items.content:
Last pod before #GW1, and our last #FPL discussions before the deadline. We just talk about whatever is on our minds with regards to our teams and the rapidly approaching deadline. We’re not ok.
Normally these Thursday episodes (Friday My Life episodes) are behind the Patreon paywall but for the episode right before GW1 we put it out for free publicly. If you want two pods a week instead of one pod a week (and discord, and livestreams, and more) then signup here: https://www.patreon.com/FMLFPL

items.content:
Walsh and Brad dive deep into decision making, cognitive biases, and mistakes that we all make (and will make again) in this game called #FPL, and ways to improve on them.
Dr. Rettler teaches philosophy and critical thinking at the University of Wyoming. He’s published 14 papers mostly on metaphysics and philosophy of religion, and has a book coming out in a few months giving a philosophical case for bitcoin.
Check him out here: www.bradleyrettler.com and here: http://resistance.money/
—

On Monday for Patreon subscribers only we’ll do the rest of the questions and whatever else and that’ll truly be the last episode of the season.

items.title: Ep. 398 - #GW29 Int’l Break - Hair Plug Italian ****

items.content:
There were only four matches but there was a ton of action and a ton of FPL points. Now we’re fucking off for ten days because it’s an international break soooo not see ya tomorrow.

All our links: https://linktr.ee/fmlfpl


 00:00 - Intro / admin

 00:50 - How’d we do in Free Hit GW30.

  07:01 - League updates.

  09:28 - Wolves vs. Leeds.

  13:17 - Villa vs. Arsenal.

  20:11 - Leicester vs. Brentham.

  22:50 - Meslier / Tying neck to goalpost.

  25:45 - Spurs stuff.

  32:42 - Questions from Discord.

  37:41 - Wildcard tinker / Wildcard tangent / Chelsea tangent.

  54:43 - Choosing FML FPL Cup knockout winners based on their FPL team names.

  01:00:01 - Outro.


Learn more about your ad choices. Visit megaphone.fm/adchoices

items.title: Ep. 340 - On to Int’l Break - Necktie

items.content:
A lot to take in with the first half of the DGW and a lot to look forward to too (or not; only 4 matches followed by an international break fucking hell). Alon’s on a -42 so far this week, so, let’s go.

All our links: https://linktr.ee/fmlfpl

Thumbnail by Cole: @ilovemonsters on Twitter and @colelovemonsters on Instagram


 00:00 - Intro / admin

 01:05 - How’re we doing in GW29.

  04:37 - Kane cap over Mo cap.

  No FML FPL Cupdates.

  No League updates.

  11:15 - Man. United vs. Spurs.

  18:00 - Spurs vs. West Ham.

  21:57 - Southampton.

  25:04 - Watford.

  26:52 - Wolves vs. Leeds.

  30:38 - Arsenal vs. Leicester.

  32:05 - Free Hit GW30 questions.

  49:29 - A few other questions from Discord.

  51:26 - Our teams and transfers and captains.

  54:09 - Thank yous and anus slap(s).

  54:56 - Little tangent on Kai (Baraka) red card shout and Chelsea’s 3 sponsorship.

  01:00:28 - Outro.

items.content:

  16:56 - Chelsea questions.

  29:18 - Foden and Brighton vs. Man. City.

  35:41 - Players we hate vs. players we love.

  38:45 - Podding as therapy / Life balance.

  40:19 - Spurs.

  47:54 - More questions from our Discord.

items.title: Ep. 317 - On to GW9 - Fantasizing About Our Fantasy Teams

items.content:
Adam is the Head of User Experience at https://fbref.com and Dan is a developer there.

Alon and the guys talk all about Football Reference, the features, how to use the site, what some of the stats mean and what they’re for, how they would build a FPL team, and more.

Hit up Adam with thoughts on FBRef @fussballtwit on Twitter, and Dan is @DanHirsch.

items.title: Ep. 313 - On to GW6 - Cough to Get Off

items.content:
Carl Anka covers Manchester United for The Athletic and he also co-wrote "You Are A Champion: Unlock Your Potential, Find Your Voice And Be The BEST You Can Be" with Marcus Rashford.

Alon and Carl talk all about Manchester United. There’s Ronaldo and how he fits into the team, Ole and what he’s up to, the direction of Manchester United, Sancho, Varane, Manchester United’s “window to win”, Business Casual, Unserious, DDG vs. Henderson, writing a book with Marcus Rashford, Carl’s FPL team, and more.


 You can find "You Are A Champion: Unlock Your Potential, Find Your Voice And Be The BEST You Can Be" by Marcus Rashford and Carl Anka at: https://www.panmacmillan.com/authors/marcus-rashford/you-are-a-champion/9781529068177


 Follow Carl on Twitter at: https://twitter.com/Ankaman616


  Check out his writing at The Athletic and get 33% off if you use this URL: https://theathletic.com/manunitedpod


  Talk of the Devils podcast: https://theathletic.com/podcast/162-talk-of-the-devils/


  And the Wrighty’s House podcast appears in the Ringer FC feed: https://open.spotify.com/show/36Ynwdxjd1TC0Z2OLFtnIm

items.title: Ep. 312 - Fireside Chat with Carl Anka

items.content:
Walsh’s Wildcard is popped and that dominates the conversation. Balancing the Mo/Rom/Ron triumvirate with enablers is crucial and we get into a bunch of more shit!


 00:00 - Intro / admin.

 01:58 - How’d we do in GW4?

  05:16 - Leagues update.

  06:01 - Walsh is on Wildcard.

  11:32 - Budget MIDs.

  24:45 - Budget and mid-priced FWDs.

  33:22 - Burnley rant.

  39:13 - Man. United and Ronaldo.

  46:59 - Lukaku.

  52:42 - Crystal Palace.

  59:30 - West Ham.

  01:04:05 - Leeds.

  01:10:27 - More questions from our Discord.

  01:13:54 - Our transfers and captains for GW5.

  01:15:19 - Walsh’s current Wildcard tinker.

  01:29:02 - Anus slap(s) and outro.

items.content:
Early season there is just so damn much to talk about for every episode. Let’s go get it.

Also shoutout to the Mitski song “I Bet on Losing Dogs” that I got the name of this episode from which A. rocks and B. describes my FPL tendencies (betting on losing dogs): https://youtu.be/dQkZve4_B2A


 00:00 - Intro / admin.

 00:48 - How’d we do in GW3?

  01:30 - Do we actually positively influence each other in FPL? Telling each other stories. Bullish and bearish.

  08:05 - Leagues update.

  08:53 - Cristiano Ronaldo and Manchester United assets.

  20:59 - Bruno cap over Antonio cap.

  23:26 - The how and why our views differ from the herd.

  24:46 - Premiums, enablers, and the death of the middle class. Two premiums or three premiums?

  34:39 - Let’s talk about Leeds.

  41:27 - Wolves questions.

  52:37 - More enablers.

  58:32 - Some Man. City chat.

  01:07:21 - Other random shit.

  01:09:31 - More questions from our Discord (and enabler forwards).

  01:26:50 - Our transfers and captains for GW4.

  01:29:34 - Anus slap(s) and outro.

items.title: Ep. 310 - On to the International Break - I Bet on Losing Dogs

items.content:
There’s too much to talk about and we go long again. We have many takes and rants and complaints and thoughts. The season is well and truly rolling and we’re already behind the template. Where to next?

 00:59 - How’d we do in GW2? And GW2 tilting things.

  09:31 - Leagues update.

  11:17 - West Ham and Antonio and Benrahma.

  18:46 - Man. City questions.

  30:36 - Spurs questions. And some Wolves chat.

  41:43 - Chelsea questions.

  51:29 - Mo + Trent + Bruno + Rom - get’em all.

  52:25 - Other forwards - DCL, Toney, Armstrong, and Callum.

items.title: Ep. 308 - On to GW2 - Mee and You

items.content:
Questions into topics into rants and tangents and rinse and repeat. It’s time for GW1 and there are infinite possibilities ahead of us. Let’s explore some.


 00:00 - Intro / admin.

 03:16 - Are we still on Bachmann?

  04:34 - Building for long term or building for short term or a bit of both?

  09:08 - Early Wildcard?

  11:41 - Liverpool / Jota / Tsimikas.

  24:21 - Amartey (and other 4.0 guys).

  29:46 - Up to forwards.

  30:22 - Ings / Villa.

  36:25 - Lukaku. Vardy?

  39:38 - Wilf.

  43:10 - Antonio and West Ham.

  51:43 - Leeds assets.

  57:54 - Man. United assets.

  01:04:42 - Discord questions.

  01:08:02 - Gundo and some City guys.

  01:35:11 - Captain for GW1.

  01:36:59 - Questions we still have for ourselves.

  01:39:58 - Anus slap(s) and outro.

items.title: Ep. 307 - Preseason Pod 4/4 - GAMEWEEK ONE BABY

items.content:
Neil Atkinson does loads of presenting, hosting, and writing for the award winning Anfield Wrap.

Alon and Neil talk about The Anfield Wrap, Liverpool, and then bounce around to different teams, players, the 21/22 season, fantasy football, and more.

You can find Neil on twitter at: https://twitter.com/Knox_Harrington

And you can find all things Anfield Wrap including their free podcasts, free videos, and free articles at: https://www.theanfieldwrap.com/


 00:00 - Intro / admin.

 00:49 - How did The Anfield Wrap start and grow?

  04:52 - Come for the football and stay for the city (Liverpool).

  07:17 - Konate, VVD, and the other Liverpool centerbacks.

  10:26 - Liverpool’s midfield.

  14:12 - Thiago Alcântara.

  15:17 - Diogo Jota, Firmino, and the ways in which Liverpool will attack.

  21:32 - Players taking time under both Pep and Klopp.

  23:09 - Liverpool becoming more physically imposing.

  24:55 - Sadio Mane and physical and mental fatigue. Also the mental strain from the pandemic on certain players.

  28:21 - Changes between last season and this season.

  31:34 - Man. City, Man. United, Chelsea and a title challenge.

  36:05 - How much new signings do or don’t move the needle.

  38:22 - The 21/22 season for Brighton, Aston Villa, Burnley, Southampton, Wolves, Crystal Palace, and Everton.

  41:53 - The top four remaining the top four.

  44:35 - The newly promoted sides.

  46:34 - What’s Neil and The Anfield Wrap’s relationship and experience with fantasy football and FPL?

  52:41 - Outro.


Links:


  Check us out at: http://fmlfpl.com


  Support us at: http://patreon.com/FMLFPL


  We’re most active on twitter: https://twitter.com/FMLFPL


  We upload video versions of the pod on youtube: https://www.youtube.com/fmlfpl


  And Alon sometimes goes live on twitch: https://www.twitch.tv/fmlfpl



Learn more about your ad choices. Visit megaphone.fm/adchoices

Neil Atkinson does loads of presenting, hosting, and writing for the award winning Anfield Wrap.

Alon and Neil talk about The Anfield Wrap, Liverpool, and then bounce around to different teams, players, the 21/22 season, fantasy football, and more.

You can find Neil on twitter at: https://twitter.com/Knox_Harrington

And you can find all things Anfield Wrap including their free podcasts, free videos, and free articles at: https://www.theanfieldwrap.com/

 00:49 - How did The Anfield Wrap start and grow?

  04:52 - Come for the football and stay for the city (Liverpool).

  07:17 - Konate, VVD, and the other Liverpool centerbacks.

  10:26 - Liverpool’s midfield.

  14:12 - Thiago Alcântara.

  15:17 - Diogo Jota, Firmino, and the ways in which Liverpool will attack.

  21:32 - Players taking time under both Pep and Klopp.

  23:09 - Liverpool becoming more physically imposing.

  24:55 - Sadio Mane and physical and mental fatigue. Also the mental strain from the pandemic on certain players.

items.title: Ep. 305 - Preseason Pod 3/4 - Budget-priced Assets

items.content:
Walsh chats with a few lads one at a time - each of them representing one of the newly promoted sides for the upcoming 21/22 Premier League season.


 You can find Bradley at: https://twitter.com/BradleyHayden11


 Jerry at: @Jerry in our Patreon Discord server.

  And Billy at: https://twitter.com/Beesotted and his podcast at http://prideofwest.london/



--


  00:00 - Intro / admin.
    
      00:53 - Watford chat with Bradley Hayden.

      01:56 - Watford’s 20/21 season.

      05:47 - Watford’s goalkeeping and defense.

      08:35 - Watford’s playing style.

      10:24 - Kiko Femenia.

      12:10 - Danny Rose.

      14:48 - Watford’s midfield three.

      18:04 - Xisco’s job.

      21:11 - Ismaila Sarr.

      24:11 - Joao Pedro.

      27:00 - Josh King.

      28:50 - Bradley outro.

    
  

  
29:51 - Norwich chat with Jerry Jamieson.
    
      30:09 - Norwich’s 20/21 season.

      31:14 - Norwich’s playing style.

      32:44 - Norwich’s goalkeeping and defense.

      39:15 - Transfers in and the midfield.

      43:03 - Todd Cantwell.

      44:29 - Milot Rashica.

      46:46 - Pukki.

      48:20 - Norwich’s opening fixtures.

      50:14 - Jerry outro.

    
  

  
50:37 - Brentford chat with Billy Grant.
    
      51:58 - Brentford’s 19/20 and 20/21 seasons.

      01:01:01 - Brentford’s formations and style.

      01:07:07 - Bryan Mbeumo.

      01:10:08 - Frank Onyeka.

      01:13:49 - Mathias Jensen.

      01:15:28 - Ivan Toney.

      01:20:28 - Opening fixtures for Brentford.

      01:22:48 - More Ivan Toney.

      01:24:07 - Billy outro.

items.title: Ep. 303 - Preseason Pod 2/4 - Mid-Priced Assets

items.content:
We are back and full of piss and vinegar. The hiatus was much needed and it’s time to sink our teeth into some preliminary FPL thoughts starting with the premium priced heavy hitters. Good to be back.


 00:00 - Intro / Admin / Autopick teams.

 04:04 - How was the break?

  06:25 - Our preseason pods breakdown.

  07:25 - Premium GKs (5.5 and up).

  22:17 - Premium DEFs (5.5 and up).

  32:55 - Alon trying to find himself.

  34:00 - Back to premium DEFs.

  47:51 - Premium MIDs (8.5 and up).

  01:11:22 - Premium FWDs (8.5 and up).

  01:26:47 - Guess Walsh’s front three - Rules: 1. “I’m gonna do good this year,” 2. “I wanna get players that I know are good at the game,” 3. “And I don’t wanna do dumb fucking idiot shit.”

  01:33:35 - Anus slap(s) and outro


Links:


  Check us out at: http://fmlfpl.com


  Support us at: http://patreon.com/FMLFPL


  We’re most active on twitter: https://twitter.com/FMLFPL


  We upload video versions of the pod on youtube: https://www.youtube.com/fmlfpl


  And Alon sometimes goes live on twitch: https://www.twitch.tv/fmlfpl

items.title: Ep. 302 - Preseason Pod 1/4 - Premium Priced Assets

items.content:
Final Euros pod for us! A short one. We reminisce about the Euros so far and Euro Fantasy while it lasted before we go into hibernation and hiatus mode leading into our #FPL preseason pods.


 00:00 - Intro / Admin

 02:26 - How’d we do in Round of 16

  06:07 - Euros league update

  06:28 - Questions from Discord

  25:48 - Belgium vs. Italy

  29:29 - How about France by the way

  32:59 - Anus slap(s) and outro

items.title: Ep. 301 - On to a Hiatus - Fantasy Is an Excellent Servant but a Terrible Master

items.content:
Not a good time for us the last two MDs so it’s time to kick it into full gear and use this final wildcard opportunity to pick the greatest team to have ever been picked! Or probably just fuck it all up and keep going down in rank… :(


 00:00 - Intro / Admin

 00:52 - How’d we do in MD3

  09:08 - Euros league update

  10:35 - With chip(s) vs. without chip(s)

  13:34 - Teams we like if you don’t have any chips left

  17:11 - Day to day captains we like

  33:37 - Loading up on favorites and other Round of 16 matchups

  45:04 - Questions from Discord

  51:35 - Building our R16 team

  01:08:32 - Anus slap(s) and outro


Check the boys out at http://fmlfpl.com || support at http://patreon.com/FMLFPL || on twitter @FMLFPL || on twitch https://www.twitch.tv/fmlfpl || on youtube https://www.youtube.com/fmlfpl || rate/review/subscribe and cheers!

items.title: Ep. 298 - On to Euros MD2 - Chaos Reigns

items.content:
We basically haven’t talked in a week and we’re just in it man. We are totally freestyling the episode no tactics just vibes. Lots of tangents and random thoughts here and there with days of more research and tinkering to come before finalizing our MD1 Euro Fantasy teams.

Patreon pod (2/2) recording Thursday night.

Also join our Fantasy Euros League!!! Code: 58OPBSKD08 Or just click here: https://gaming.uefa.com/en/uefaeuro2020fantasyfootball/leagues/58OPBSKD08/0046004D004C002000460050004C/FML%20FPL

items.title: Ep. 297 - Getting Ready for Euros 1/2 - The Madness Has Begun

items.content:
We cover a ton of topics and also do lots of ranting and tangenting and projecting and moaning. It’s sorta all over the place but hey this season was a shit-show and Walsh had his second worst season ever and Alon had his worst season ever so it should be all over the place, right? Let’s go.


 00:00 - Intro / Admin

 00:51 - How’d we do in GW38

  04:15 - League updates

  05:36 - What CAN we learn from season to season? And what to unlearn from COVID season?

  09:54 - Pressers

  11:35 - Point distribution / Glue guys / Yo-yoing premiums

  17:58 - First on the bench / Auto-subs

  23:28 - Theo Epstein episode / Gut calls / The unknown

  27:56 - Unsustainable bandwagons / Form and confidence

  37:19 - Man. City questions

  39:43 - Walsh maverick / How to handle the beginning of the season / Facts

  49:37 - Questions from Discord

  01:04:01 - Anus Slap(s) and Outro


WGTA Thread I referenced on the pod: https://twitter.com/WGTA_FPL/status/1397932630625198081

Theo Epstein on Bill Simmons’ Podcast we mentioned multiple times on the pod (skip the NBA part Theo part starts after 30 minutes): https://www.theringer.com/the-bill-simmons-podcast/2021/5/7/22424308/best-nba-late-season-story-lines

items.title: Ep. 257 - On to GW1 - SHOWTIME BABY!!!

items.content:

items.title: Ep. 118 - On to GW17 with Cheeky Little Dry Throats

items.content:
Yes, Fantasy Premier League is a marathon not a sprint. It's true. But what happens if while you're marathoning you feel dehydrated and your legs are jello and your lungs are wheezing and you're wishing that it was a fucking sprint so it'd already be over... Seems not good. Like us. We're not good. Fuck. Last pod of 2016! Santa Claus AKA Toby Alderweireld diarrhea'd and threw up green arrows for us in a hectic set of Boxing Day fixtures so we're pleased. A lot of team structure and looking ahead to an absolutely ludicrous GW19/GW20 schedule where there are 0 days off between the GWs and most teams in the league have only one day off between their matches. We'll see what happens but we expect a bloodbath. Let's prep... Check us out at http://fmlfpl.com || join our #FPL league - 41057-15509 || we're on twatter @FMLFPL || email us questions fmlfpl@gmail || rate/review/subscribe on iTunes || like on Facebook and cheers!

items.title: Ep. 75 - On to GW19 and GW20 with A Taste of Green

items.content:
The sadness feels perpetual in this moment. The red arrows go for as far as the eye can see... Walsh asks, "What does a green arrow look like? What does a green arrow feel like?" And who knows? We surely don't. But, alas, we put our rally caps on and try to spin things positively to get thru the rest of the week until more FPL. Hopefully FPL bringing treats this time around... items.title: Ep. 74 - On to GW18 with Gun Not Stressball

items.content:
We're sinking and we're sinking fast. Alon hits his lowest overall rank since GW6 and Walsh hits his lowest since GW7... At least we ride together / die together. It's been brutal though. We're picking the wrong guys and we have to look at ourselves in the mirror. Are we being too passive? Too conservative? Wrong team structure? It's a philosophical pod as we strive to find our stupid fucking feet. items.title: Ep. 73 - On To GW17 with Blanks & Red Arrows Galore

items.content:
You either die with a 5 digit rank or live long enough to see yourself become a casual. Listen, it didn't come off for us this week and the mood is... gloomy. But we get in there, we cover the major happenings, we look ahead, and mistakes were made but we try to dissuade you all from making the same errors that we've made. Another pod coming midweek Wednesday night after the midweek GW and we go from there. Tag along. items.title: Ep. 71 - On To GW15 with Template Taking Shape

items.content:
So many big hitters and so little time. And so little funds... We collectively as a community have to deal with our fallen friend Philippe the little magician and move on. We have to get Kane. We have to get Kun. We have to get Diego. We have to get Zlatan. And Alexis. And Chelsea defenders, but also Totty defenders. And Cedric. Wait holy fuck there are SO MANY GOOD GUYS AND NO TEMPLATE! THIS SEASON IS WEIRD BUT FUN!!!!!! items.content:
Fireside Chat with internet artist and "soccer freak" Petra Cortright! We're taking the week off from normal Fantasy Premier League duties because of ANOTHER international break (we'll be back to normal early next week) so instead we invited our friend Petra on to talk about her history with soccer, the prem, USA soccer, women's soccer, and more! items.title: Ep. 67 - Fireside Chat with Petra Cortright

items.content:
Mids mids mids mids mids. We're blowing up the midfield. Is FEO no longer our lord and savior? Is Wee Joe real? Is Gundogan God? The strike force seems a known entity, captains are already written, so we go elsewhere and dive deep. And with ANOTHER international break on the horizon we brace ourselves for the melancholy and infinite sadness and try to just have fun out there. Join us. Check us out at fmlfpl.com || join our #FPL league - 41057-15509 || we're on twatter @FMLFPL || email us questions fmlfpl@gmail || rate us on iTunes || like on Facebook and cheers!

items.title: Ep. 66 - On To GW11 with Cheapies in Midfield

items.content:
Things keep kind of going as planned which means we should be scared right? Something will surely screw us over in the coming weeks? I don't know. We still can't nail down a captain and we're unsure of the league's most sure thing in Kun Aguero but our teams are good. The post-wildcard era has been sweet to us as green arrows keep blooming so we'll keep rolling. Laissez les bons temps rouler. items.title: Ep. 62 - On To GW7 with a Baguette

items.content:
If an expert is a person who has made all the mistakes that can be made in a very narrow field then without a doubt we are a couple of dickhead Fantasy Premier League experts. Another week in the slums has left us with no other choice but to pop our ultimate ability of Wildcarding. This pod we basically both blacked out and talked about our own teams / wildcard squads for fifty hours and then cut it down to an hour and a quarter. All the best... items.title: Ep. 59 - On To GW4 with or without Elbow Man

items.content:
Fireside chat with neuroscientist Dr. Renee Miller the author of "Cognitive Bias in Fantasy Sports: Is Your Brain Sabotaging Your Team?" In essence the #FPL season is a series of decisions we make with our squads. The hope is that becoming aware of some of these major biases and fallacies will improve said decision making by employing a less biased approach to our Fantasy Premier League teams. || Buy Renee's book here: https://gumroad.com/reneemiller01 || This episode is sponsored by "The Stars' Fault": https://amzn.com/B01K5RT0QM || Check us out at http://fmlfpl.com || join our FPL league - 41057-15509 || we're on twatter @FMLFPL || email us questions fmlfpl@gmail || rate us on iTunes || like on Facebook and cheers!

items.title: Ep. 51 - Fireside Chat with Jamie Smith

items.content:
It's the final match for UEFA Euro Fantasy 2016 and we do our part to converse and figure out a strategy, only to then ignore it and fuck ourselves over... Shit... But yes France v Portugal will be amazing, and even more amazing is FPL (Fantasy Premier League) is coming very soon. We can hardly wait. This is a nice 'n' tidy episode with very little to talk about. We make the best of it :)

items.title: Ep. 49 - Patiently Waiting

items.content:
As the player pool diminishes our enthusiasm kind of goes with it. The matches have been fantastic but Fantasy Euros just doesn't give us the same feels as a full season of Fantasy Premier League which is now around the corner. Hence only 'Semi Al Dente'... We make some picks for the semis and try and navigate the gridlock to find some potential differentials and clean sheets, if there are any at this point!

items.title: Ep. 48 - Semi Al Dente

items.content:
The round of 16 didn't bring us any glory but it's ok because we have ANOTHER WILDCARD TO TIT THE QUARTERS WITH!!! Yes folks. We cover what's happening, who we like and hate and all the rest, while also going through tinker town putting together our 15-man holy grail squadron that will carry us into the clouds. Only eight teams left to choose from... You must choose, but choose wisely.... for as the true grail will give you life, the false life will take it from you....

items.title: Ep. 47 - You Must Choose But Choose Wisely

items.content:
Trying to wade through a truckload of opinions and stats and configurations on our first wildcard of this beautiful tournament. Fantasy Euros is in full flight and it feels as though we're onto the next round along side the qualifying teams. It really is... a fantasy. We cover our round of 16 picks, who we like, some guys we hate, and the usual banter featuring Producer Nate and Guest Jason in for Walsh.

items.title: Ep. 46 - Dropped By Dog

items.content:
Wildcards on roses and transfers on tittens, bright copper todfests and warm woolen captains. Ok I need to calm down, but I can't! I'm al dente and it's exciting times! We had a dongfest of a week, we have two free transfers to play with, we're saving our wildcard (and why) and much much more in this Gameweek 3 ("Matchday 3") UEFA Euro Fantasy preview.

items.title: Ep. 45 - Wildcards On Roses and Transfers On Tittens

items.content:
The week isn't even fucking over yet and we're fully diving into the UEFA Euro 2016 Fantasy Fuckfest. This is a wild uproar of the full emotional spectrum featuring love, hate, commitment, desire, disgust, and more. We close our eyes and try to recount all of what the fuck happened in an incredible first week of Euro matches, plan ahead to Gameweek 2 ("Matchday 2") with our picks for captains/cleans, and find all of the pockets and acres of space.

items.title: Ep. 44 - Banter Buffet

items.content:
We've lulled long enough. Euros are here and fantasy is back. This episode feels like a hunkering down; two men finding shelter in a squall. Our 15-man UEFA Euro Fantasy squad is rounding up, our team structure and money allocation feel safe, and we're still having fun. You gotta have fucking fun. Now let's score some points and soar into ecstasy together. *Don't forget* to join our Euro Fantasy league ASAP! League info: fmlfpl.com/leagues

items.title: Ep. 42 - Preliminary Al Dente

items.content:
The Fantasy Premier League season finalé pod is a deep pool of reflection where we try and pick out important lessons learned from the '15/'16 season of FPL and take it from there. We have some laughs, some good memories, some shit memories - so life goes. After this ep. will come a 2-3 week hiatus before we kick off with FML FEL - our #EuroFantasy / #FantasyEuro podcast. Check http://fmlfpl.com/ for league info and much much more!

Missing the Yang to my Yin the pod still must go on as we go full penetration raw dog into the rapidly upcoming double gameweeks, blank gameweeks, and wildcard bonanzas. items.title: Ep. 27 - We're All Just Weathermen

items.content:
Template v1.0 strikes again with the usual suspects Algerian Messi and German Praying Mantis with double digit hauls and just like that they are back in our good graces. Have we just been trying to be too cute and too clever this season? Our ranks say yes, our hearts and minds say fuck off. Leicester fly, City stumble, Spurs look unstoppable, and Arsenal show some old signs of life. Come hang with us, listeners, for another episode of FML FPL. items.title: Ep. 11 - A Fatal International Break

items.content:
Welp, Alexis finally woke up while Aguero remained in his season long coma as GW7 came to a close. A weekend blighted by that Cherry, Callum Wilson, crumbling to the pitch in agony like a bag of bones has many a fantasy manager scrambling for a replacement. Costa gets ready to post up next to Ibramovich as they duel it out for worst dressed in the Chelsea stands over their next couple and we get into City's stunning loss to Wenger's chain smoking mate and brother from another Eastern European mother, Slavan Bilic. It's all here, and more, in this episode of FML FPL. Don't forget to join our league ID: 177490-742547 - we hope to see you there. Mail us your RMTs at fmlfpl@gmail.com and don't forget to twit us @fmlfpl for all Fantasy Premier League needs.

items.title: Ep. 9 - Martial Arts

items.content:
GW5 is in the books and we keep at it in trying to unpack this tumultuous season. The budgetary options continue to fire while the premiums keep blanking...woe is us. It seems like you either pick your clean sheets correct or end up with a big red arrow. We get stuck in looking forward towards GW6 in a hope to finally hit on captaincy to propel us through the rankings. Don't forget to join our league ID: 177490-742547 - we hope to see you there. Mail us your RMTs at fmlfpl@gmail.com and don't forget to twit us @fmlfpl for all Fantasy Premier League needs.

items.title: Ep. 8 - Good Players Suck

items.content:
As we watch the first international break die a slow and excruciating death your hosts turn their attentions towards Gameweek 5. In what seems like decades ago, we recap the action from GW4 and cry a little into our beers for yet another Aguero captaincy blank and a couple of low scores. But, we try to keep our youthful, yank perkiness and optimism as we look forward! We cover the usual RMT, get into what the fuck happened last week, and then wrap up with GW5 captaincy, clean sheets, and finally a quick review of our teams. Don't forget to join our league ID: 177490-742547 - we hope to see you there. Mail us your RMTs at fmlfpl@gmail.com and don't forget to twit us @fmlfpl for all Fantasy Premier League needs.

items.title: Ep. 7 - We Are Back

items.content:
Ahead of the saddest time of all - an international break - we hit on our usual agenda while also adding a new segment called 'what the fuck happened last week' where we cover salient FPL talking points as we see them from the weekend. In your hosts' constant effort to improve the pod we took some listener suggestions...we shortened the user submitted RMT section and worked on saying "like" less! Don't forget to join our league ID: 177490-742547 - we hope to see you there. Mail us your RMTs at fmlfpl@gmail.com and don't forget to twit us @fmlfpl for all Fantasy Premier League needs.

items.title: Ep. 6 - WTF Price Fluctuation

items.content:
Gameweek 2 has come and gone and seemingly rewarded knee jerkers as many of those GW1 scorers kept it up. Bandwagons have firmly emerged...but which of them are for real and which are flashes in the pan? We discuss this, a user submitted RMT, price changes, clean sheets, and captaincy options. Join us as we experience the emotional ebbs and flows of GW2 and how our teams are faring as well moving forward. Don't forget to join our league ID: 177490-742547 - we hope to see you there. Mail us your RMTs at fmlfpl@gmail.com and don't forget to twit us @fmlfpl for all Fantasy Premier League needs.
